.TH cheat 1
.SH NAME
cheat \- create and view command-line cheatsheets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cheat
[options] [<cheatsheet>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cheat
allows you to create and view interactive cheatsheets on the command-line. It was designed to help remind *nix system administrators of options for commands that they use frequently, but not frequently enough to remember.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-colorize
Colorize output. Apply syntax-highlighting to code samples, and highlight to search matches.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-directories
List the directories in which cheatsheets are stored.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-edit =\fISHEET\fR
Open \fISHEET\fR for editing.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List all available cheatsheets.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path =\fINAME\fR
Filter to cheatsheets on path \fINAME\fR.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-regex
Treat search \fIPHRASE\fR as a regular expression.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-search =\fIPHRASE\fR
Search all cheatsheets for \fIPHRASE\fR.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-tag=\fITAG\fR
Return only cheatsheets matching \fITAG\fR.
.TP
.BR \-T ", " \-\-Tags
List all tags in use within cheatsheets.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display the \fBcheat\fR version.
.TP
.BR \-\-rm=\fISHEET\fR
Removes (deletes) \fISHEET\fR from the filesystem.
.SH OPTIONS
.SH FILES
.SH EXAMPLES
